      "writtenOn": "2026-07-14T23:43:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Not a deadlock: mutex_ is a std::recursive_mutex (rtp_session.h:72), not a plain std::mutex, so re-locking it from the same thread is well-defined. The exact same lock-then-restartSender() pattern already ships in setMuted(): it takes the lock (video_rtp_session.cpp:500) and calls restartSender() (line 519), which re-locks at line 271. conferenceFormatChanged() runs on the same call path (Conference::onMixerFormatChanged, via runOnMainThread), so restartSender() and sender_-\u003esetBitrate() simply re-enter the recursive mutex on the owning thread. No lock is held across another thread here.",
